 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Junior Ride & Drive and Manual Test Engineer Capgemini 8,227 reviews Peachtree City, GA Capgemini 8,227 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Contract Full Job Description Duration :8+Months 
Responsibilities : 
Support Ride and Drive Testing 
Driving for long hours (~5 hrs) per day (80%) 
Testing as per process, manual testing (20%) 
Understanding test plan and use-cases for in-vehicle testing 
Requirement analysis, Design and development, documentation of test cases 
Defect reproduction based on limited information from user/ client 
Open to short domestic travel to automobile factories or warehouses and support working development and testing teams 
Communication with internal and external stakeholders 
Required skills : 
Bachelor\'s degree in Computer/Electronics/Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, or related 
2+ years of relevant experience in executing a test plan, identify gaps and developing simple test cases 
2+ years of relevant experience in Testing (preferred Automotive domain) 
Must have valid Driver\'s license and be a safe driver 
Experience in software testing for infotainment system or consumer electronics products 
Must have knowledge and experience of types of testing (e.g. normal, boundary, abnormal, load testing) 
Good analytical and communication skills 
Knowledge and experience in automotive domain is a plus 
Working knowledge of a Test Development Life Cycle (TDLC). 
